graphite2
------------------------------------------
Graphite2 is a project within SIL's Non-Roman Script Initiative and Language
Software Development groups to provide rendering capabilities for complex
non-Roman writing systems. Graphite can be used to create "smart fonts"
capable of displaying writing systems with various complex behaviors. With
respect to the Text Encoding Model, Graphite handles the "Rendering" aspect of
writing system implementation.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.9-1
  libgcc1-4.5.3-2
  libiconv2-1.14-1
  libicu48-4.8.1-1
  libstdc++6-4.5.3-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.21.53-2
  cmake-2.8.4-1
  cygport-0.10.5-1
  gawk-3.1.8-1
  gcc4-core-4.5.3-2
  gcc4-g++-4.5.3-2
  libtool-2.4-1
  make-3.81-2

Canonical website:
  http://silgraphite.sf.net/

Canonical download:
  mirror://sourceforge/silgraphite/graphite2-1.0.3.tgz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack graphite2-1.0.3-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./graphite2-1.0.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/graphite2-1.0.3-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/graphite2-1.0.3-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libgraphite2_2.0.0-1.0.3-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libgraphite2-devel-1.0.3-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(graphite2)
  /usr/bin/comparerenderer.exe
  /usr/bin/gr2fonttest.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/graphite2.README
  /usr/share/doc/graphite2/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/graphite2/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/graphite2/LICENSE

(libgraphite2_2.0.0)
  /usr/bin/cyggraphite2-2.0.0.dll

(libgraphite2-devel)
  /usr/include/graphite2/Font.h
  /usr/include/graphite2/Segment.h
  /usr/include/graphite2/Types.h
  /usr/lib/libgraphite2.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/graphite2.pc
  /usr/share/graphite2/graphite2-release.cmake
  /usr/share/graphite2/graphite2.cmake

